Java language



Java is a modern language and has many features to deal with files. ListingÂ C.1 illustrates writing and reading a file with float samples using a small header, which informs the number of samples. Recall that Java always uses big-endian. The output file has a size of 22 bytes, corresponding to 5 float (4-bytes) samples plus the 2-bytes header.



